    skos:prefLabel "Land degradation is a pervasive. systemic phenomenon: it occurs in all parts of the terrestrial world and can take many forms." .

<http://ontology.ipbes.net/report/il/LDR18-figureSPM10> a ipbes:Illustration ;
    dcterms:identifier "Figure SPM10" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Land degradation can occur either through a loss of biodiversity. ecosystem functions or services. without a change in land cover class or use (1). or by the transformation to a derived ecosystem type such as the conversion of natural cover to a crop field (2). delivering a different spectrum of benefits. but also typically involving loss of biodiversity and reduction of some ecosystem functions and services." .

