    ipbes:Report <http://ontology.ipbes.net/report/LDR18> ;
    ipbes:hasDescription """
DOCUMENT_PREFERENCES <data data-version="3" zotero-version="7.0.30"><session id="rhU4CYSc"/><style id="http://www.zotero.org/styles/apa" locale="en-GB" hasBibliography="1" bibliographyStyleHasBeenSet="0"/><prefs><pref name="fieldType" value="Field"/></prefs></data>
1 On this biodiversity section, all % should be read as per cent points.
2 Worldwide, consumption patterns slowly converge to 50% above the consumption level suggested by a ‘Healthy Diet’ (daily per capita intake of 10 g beef, 10 g pork, and 46.6 g of chicken meat and eggs), the so-called Willet-diet . 
3 Baseline yield improvement are increased by 50% in OECD countries to a maximum increase of 1.5% per year. 
